Package: dlcompat
Version: 20010123
Revision: 2
Source: http://download.sourceforge.net/fink/%n-%v.tar.gz
CompileScript: make prefix=%p
InstallScript: make install prefix=%i
 if [ x`whoami` = xroot -a -f /usr/local/lib/libdl.dylib ]; then rm -f /usr/local/include/dlfcn.h /usr/local/lib/libdl.a /usr/local/lib/libdl.dylib ; ln -s %p/lib/libdl.dylib /usr/local/lib ; fi
 if [ x`whoami` != xroot -a -f /usr/local/lib/libdl.dylib ]; then sudo sh -c 'rm -f /usr/local/include/dlfcn.h /usr/local/lib/libdl.a /usr/local/lib/libdl.dylib ; ln -s %p/lib/libdl.dylib /usr/local/lib' ; fi
CommentPort: Doesn't use autoconf, just a Darwin-specific
 Makefile. Will try to use sudo to install a compatibility symlink in
 /usr/local/lib if neccessary.
CommentStow: Previous revisions installed the package in
 /usr/local. This is no longer the case. When upgrading, this package
 will remove the include file and library in /usr/local and put a
 compatibility symlink there (for binaries linked against the older
 package). It doesn't do this on first installs, so new users no
 longer need to setup sudo.
Maintainer: Christoph Pfisterer <chrisp@users.sourceforge.net>
